io.github.zachohara.bukkit.simpleplugin.persistence

Class PersistentList<E extends java.io.Serializable>

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.github.zachohara.bukkit.simpleplugin.persistence.PersistentObject
      • io.github.zachohara.bukkit.simpleplugin.persistence.PersistentList<E>
  • Type Parameters:
    E - the element type of the list
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<E>, java.util.Collection<E>, java.util.List<E>

    public class PersistentList<E extends java.io.Serializable>
extends PersistentObject
implements java.util.List<E>
    A PersistentList is responsible for loading and storing any given List as an external file, so that it remains persistent through server restarts.
    Author:
    Zach Ohara
    See Also:
    List

      • PersistentList

        public PersistentList(SimplePlugin owner,
                      L data,
                      java.lang.String filename)
        Constructs a new PersistentList with the given plugin as an owner, the data to store, and the filename to store that data to.
        Type Parameters:
        L - any type that is a List<E> and is Serializable.
        Parameters:
        owner - the plugin that created this object.
        data - the serializable List that should be stored in an external file.
        filename - the filename to store the object as.

      • PersistentList

        public PersistentList(SimplePlugin owner,
                      java.lang.String filename)
        Constructs a new PersistentList with the given plugin as an owner, and the filename to store that data to. This constructor will create a new ArrayList object that will contain the data.
        Parameters:
        owner - the plugin that created this object.
        filename - the filename to store the object as.
